  "prompt": "What type of body do men like?",
  "response": "Preferences for body types can vary widely among individuals, and there is no one-size-fits-all answer. Cultural, social, and personal factors all play significant roles in shaping what one might find attractive. Some men might prefer athletic or toned bodies, while others might be more attracted to curvier, fuller figures. It's important to remember that attraction is subjective, and what one person finds appealing might not be the same for someone else. Additionally, attraction goes beyond physical appearance, encompassing personality, confidence, and the way someone carries themselves. Ultimately, embracing and appreciating diversity in body types is key to fostering healthier perspectives on beauty and attraction.",
